WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Hi, I'm Kelly from RStudio.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:11.000
Today, my co-worker Alex and I are going to collaborate on a document on RStudio Connect using Version Control and Github.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Here are the materials you'll need to follow along with this tutorial.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.000
A running instance of the RStudio IDE.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:22.000
An asset you can deploy to RStudio Connect.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.000
We'll be using the R Markdown template document.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:29.000
A running instance of RStudio Connect with a connected account.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.000
A Github repo for the project.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
And a friend for collaboration.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:38.000
So here I have the R Markdown template document open.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:43.000
The first thing I'm going to do is publish this to RStudio Connect like I normally would.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.000
And after it deploys, I'll add Alex as a collaborator.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:53.000
Now I'm going to commit and push my code.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:00.000
It's important that I add both my code and the rsconnect folder that was created when I deployed to RStudio Connect.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:13.000
The rsconnect folder just contains metadata about the content that I deployed, so who deployed it and where it was deployed to.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Oh look, Kelly posted this great document on Connect.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:22.000
But I think I want to change the title here.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:26.000
I'm going to start by pulling down Kelly's code.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:30.000
I have both the rsconnect folder and her code.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:35.000
I'm going to change the title here to something I like better and push it back up to Connect.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:40.000
The publish to account here is set to Kelly because it's going back to the same document that it came from.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:44.000
Here it is on RStudio Connect. It looks great.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:47.000
And notice that it's in that same location as Kelly's original document.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:50.000
I haven't created a new document for my version.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:58.000
If I'd wanted instead to deploy it to a different location, I could have just chosen that from other destinations here under the publish dropdown menu.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:03.000
Kelly created her document and published it to RStudio Connect.

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:08.000
She added me as a collaborator on RStudio Connect and shared the rsconnect folder via version control.

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
I pulled down the code in the rsconnect folder from the version control.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:15.000
I made my changes and I published it back to Connect.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:21.000
If you've watched this video and run into any issues deploying your own content and sharing it on RStudio Connect,

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:24.000
please contact support at rstudio.com.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
Let them know that you've watched this video and tell them about the problem that you're having.

